**SUSTAINABLE TECHNOLOGY ADOPTION SCORE: 74/100**

Technology Adoption: 22/25  
Innovation Leadership: 18/25  
Measurable Impact: 14/25  
Future Strategy: 13/15  
Industry Position: 7/10

Summary assessment: Micron has implemented multiple significant sustainable technologies at site scale (renewables procurement and on-site solar, water reuse, zero‑GWP coolants, energy‑efficient product lines) and backed them with substantive financing and targets. The company shows strong operational integration and measurable wins (renewable electricity coverage in several countries; water reuse up to 66%; product power reductions), plus an explicit roadmap and capital commitments. It is an above‑average industry performer with clear innovation activity and partnerships, but it is not the single sustainability leader among the largest semiconductor peers (TSMC, Samsung, Intel) and has not yet delivered very large (>>25%) company‑wide emissions reductions—hence the 74/100 overall score.

Findings and justification (by research area)

