Caveats and gaps
- Public reporting shows strong progress on scope 1 and site‑level metrics, but scope 3 targets and supplier emissions remain areas that require continued scaling across the supply chain—Micron is active on supplier engagement, but large scope‑3 decarbonization is inherently complex [Micron (2-9)](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEETxwmtQvnbLxC5CG1iC4o_-BNRnWaUBO8XUW8IsCEChJ4oBR8ux-hqb0JjP5CUxopcwu6bSFnvg82nRR1fIF9iVh5WN68nZgJ0WyFc-ttsNfegOZ4B8t7Wu1IAYlI1g_XhcHI5nfa_nMZRLzTMTAHjrhnMGHJyfmVKydBPn6D9bVuj8oSFpIl3C-8UVFYAYaLVdqVyrueqyCv96mVoeigLIQCtJQ=) [stocktitan (2-4)](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEWT4KUU4kmSKMtxyks-EeFPO9CUiVFRYxf9iLQEyinDcIJxqfBrFRMXx6bjvBUo44ajcvH8RQmYS-oVaGfuc4MKnA-TsYsV3mLvQm8Lb8eam3x5_06EwtRD07WmnfJ9lTOG1XF0pyeIdVG4H8SOvRj4sKpcG_R6EA4qd7mOO0UHd-XebwVrQ81fvh1m7OLXqsw2QJVwFxGpJ6zyS9U8CikkIiPviNOQTPhGw==).
- Some advanced onsite technologies (e.g., heat recovery/CHP systems, wide energy storage rollouts) are not prominently disclosed at scale in the public domain as of the latest reports; the company focuses more on renewables procurement, coolant/process gas transitions, water tech pilots and energy‑efficient product development [Micron (3-12)](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHx1e608p3_jj8nXFjvMCQucT2PsgPwy9V2q-3LpPA20-svGmdpyFX74ANXkndr5VHOZbMHtUvf-uvfk2Unq-YynYN7eDjqQ8grWzEi7Gs9eN-kX3MY8PumzwNDUTozaGYV_E8=) [Micron (3-17)](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHWvItmSAsvD9kxSmXjjGuWG1vdWmRsfmLrgDQf47UDLHBxhVaaood9KailSszd2EBbxOOOcl2HMWK4xftVTsFxvDmBJu5MmzY_HgQFc21-k4iIAXEA5NU99gdlOntykdFvcT3QM99jDoehuOBe8EJV4AMQZYYhrNc5P_ZIgfGaXJDimUw1okBc2x69qKBg6iejYb61aGOSNqNPtvpaGUIP2xoVse5yIfAMPGGlDhveMDVJs1R8ffU2KLGsVuPXZOcoord7yQBQNBOI1WI-exRG).

